Singer and activist, Charly Boy aka Area Fada has stated what he’ll do if the presidential candidates of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Atiku Abubakar or All Progressives Congress (APC) Asiwaju Bola TInubu wins the 2023 presidential poll. The maverick entertainer made this known after Tinubu was declared winner of the APC presidential primary. The National Leader of the ruling party on Wednesday clinched the presidential ticket of the ruling party for the 2023 general elections. He defeated 13 other aspirants with 1,271 votes as against his closest rival, former Minister of Transportation Rotimi Amaechi who had 316 votes.   Why I’m never getting married, by Timaya     Five Nigerian female artistes with international recognition     Why men discourage girl child education, by Wofaifada   On May 28, the former Vice-President, Atiku Abubakar, emerged PDP presidential candidate for the 2023 election. Atiku polled  371 out of the 767 accredited votes to defeat his closest rival, Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike,  who polled 237 votes. Reacting, Area Fada vowed to leave Nigeria for Ghana should either of them eventually becomes president. The veteran showbiz man shared a photo collage of the duo with the caption: “If any of these two jabagantis win, I go just leave una walker go Ghana, go beg dem for citizenship. “Buhari, will look like a saint,” he added.